		</div>
	</form>
</div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="container">
		
    <div class="article-contributor-photo-section background-grey background-box-shadow --bottom">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row article-contributor-photo-reverse">
          <div class="col-12 col-md-8 flex --direction-col --justify-content-center article-contributor-main">
            <div class="article-contributor__meta-container">
              <h1 class="article-contributor-section_title">Adachioma Ezeano</h1>
              <p class="article-contributor-section_content">Adachioma Ezeano is a fiction writer and screenwriter who co-wrote the TV series, <em>Agoodjie</em>, for Canal+ and StudioCanal. She is a 2021 O. Henry Prize recipient and a 2023 Best of the Net winner. Her short stories have appeared in <em>Granta</em>,<em> </em><em>McSweeney’s Quarterly Concern</em>, <em>The McSweeney’s Anthology of Contemporary Literature</em>, and <em>Guernica </em>and have been translated into Italian and Bengali.</p>
              <a class="article-contributor-section_link" href="https://granta.com/adachioma-ezeano">More about the author →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
                  </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  

	</div>
</div>
</div>

